CUSTOMER SALES ANALYSIS REPORT
📌 Project Overview

This project focuses on analyzing customer purchasing behavior and sales performance using advanced Pandas operations. The analysis includes data cleaning, aggregation, pivot tables, trend analysis, customer segmentation, and business insights.

The objective of this project is to identify valuable customers, understand sales trends, analyze regional performance, and improve customer retention strategies.

📂 Dataset Information

The dataset contains sales transaction details with the following columns:

Date
Product
Quantity
Price
Customer_ID
Region

The dataset was analyzed using Python libraries including:

Pandas
NumPy
Matplotlib
Seaborn
📊 Data Cleaning & Preparation

The following preprocessing steps were performed:

Converted date columns into datetime format
Removed duplicate records
Handled missing values
Created calculated revenue columns
Extracted Year, Month, and Day from dates
Applied string operations for text transformation
📈 Analysis Performed
1. Customer Analysis

Customer purchasing patterns were analyzed to identify:

Top customers by revenue
Repeat customers
Customer lifetime value
Customer purchase frequency
Key Finding

A small percentage of customers generated the majority of total revenue, indicating strong repeat customer behavior.

2. Sales Trend Analysis

Sales data was grouped by month to identify seasonal trends.

Key Finding

Sales were highest during festive and year-end months, especially December.

3. Product Performance Analysis

Products were analyzed based on:

Total quantity sold
Revenue generated
Product demand trends
Key Finding

Electronics and laptop-related products generated the highest revenue.

4. Regional Sales Analysis

Sales were grouped by region to identify top-performing areas.

Key Finding

The South region achieved the highest overall revenue and customer activity.

5. Cross-Selling Analysis

Cross-selling opportunities were identified using grouped customer-product combinations.

Key Finding

Accessories and electronics products were frequently purchased together.

📋 Pivot Table Summary

Pivot tables were created to summarize:

Revenue by region
Product-wise sales
Category-level performance

These tables helped in quickly comparing business performance across multiple dimensions.

📊 Visualizations Created

The project dashboard included:

Monthly Sales Trend Line Chart
Top Products Bar Chart
Regional Sales Pie Chart
Heatmap using Pivot Tables
Top Customer Revenue Chart

These visualizations provided better understanding of sales behavior and customer trends.

